Problem: Given a sorted array of n integers, remove duplicates in-place. Print only unique elements in order.

Input:
- First line: integer n
- Second line: n space-separated integers (sorted array)

Output:
- Print unique elements only, space-separated

Example:
Input:
6
1 1 2 2 3 3

Output:
1 2 3

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

code:
#include <stdio.h>

int main()
{
    int n;
    scanf("%d", &n);

    int arr[n];

    // Input array
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        scanf("%d", &arr[i]);

    // Remove duplicates
    int i = 0;
    for(int j = 1; j < n; j++)
    {
        if(arr[j] != arr[i])
        {
            i++;
            arr[i] = arr[j];
        }
    }

    // Print unique elements
    for(int k = 0; k <= i; k++)
        printf("%d ", arr[k]);

    return 0;
}
